feedback: I was more tempted in every round to simply accept the suggested budget before I noticed I receive the left overs of the budget.

At the beginning of the experiment, I was highly focused, carefully reading the rules, and I even wrote down the results of the first three rounds to develop a strategy that would have maximized my private wealth and the firm's profit. Later, I realized that the firm couldn't go bankrupt, so I started requesting 6000 Talers each time to maximize my budget. That's when I stopped writing down results, and by the end of the tenth round, I didn't even accurately remember my final outcome.

I dont remember my values, sorry if this casues inconvienence. Very interesting game, somewhat funny that once value for manufacturing went over or equal 5$ the company still persist to "give" me money and continue producing.
